comments.body:
@harche thanks for running with this.  For Podman we have what I call 3 "By Hand" tests.  They're just quick tests that we run against new releases prior to release to make sure things haven't fallen over.  They are not run automatically in the CI system, only after somebody drops them somewhere and runs them directly.

They all live in Podman's /test directory and are test_podman_*.sh where * equals baseline, build or pods.

FWIW, we have similar tests in Buildah's /tests directory (note plural there).
